This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-seeed-reterminal layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Dependencies
============

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/agherzan/meta-raspberrypi.git
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/meta-qt5/meta-qt5.git
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/openembedded/meta-openembedded.git
  branch: master

  URI: https://github.com/openembedded/openembedded-core.git
  branch: master

Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the meta-seeed-reterminal layer to the xxxx mailing list (xxxx@zzzz.org)
and cc: the maintainer:

Maintainer: XXX YYYYYY <xxx.yyyyyy@zzzzz.com>

Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-seeed-reterminal layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the meta-seeed-reterminal layer to your build
=================================================

Run 'bitbake-layers add-layer meta-seeed-reterminal'

II. Misc
========
When you add all the dependencies above.
Check your build/conf/bblayers.conf

The following is mine:
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-poky \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-yocto-bsp \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-raspberrypi \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-seeed-reterminal \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-qt5 \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-openembedded/meta-oe \
  /home/xiongjian/source_code/yocto/poky/meta-openembedded/meta-python \

Then modify the build/conf/local.conf:
add 
"MACHINE ??= "raspberrypi4-64" ",
"RPI_KERNEL_DEVICETREE_OVERLAYS_append = " overlays/reTerminal.dtbo" "
"PACKAGECONFIG_append_pn-qtbase = " eglfs " "
to local.conf

Now it's time to build the image with:
"bitbake rpi-basic-image"

After several hours of compiling.
You can get the image in "build/tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi4-64"
with  .wic.bz2 suffix.
